frameDefinitions: A Recipient comes into possession of the Theme as a result of the joint action of the Donor and the Recipient.
An Agent begins preventing a Captive from moving despite a tendency or desire on the part of the Captive to do so.
A Topical_entity has properties which are affected by the existence and association of an Entity.
This frame contains perception words whose Perceivers have perceptual experiences that they do not necessarily intend to.
A volitionally acting Interceptor takes control, without being authorized to do so by the sender, of a Theme that is underway from a sender to a recipient.
frameExamples: I <t>recieved</t> a box from him in the mail.
Authorities recently <t>captured</t> several suspects who were hiding in a remote mountain area.
By the 1920s a characteristic book <t>had</t> black and white photographic illustrations only .
Abashed, realising that he had <t>overheard</t> her conversation with Victoria, Sheeley didn't try to make excuses.
Police <t>intercepted</t> the call and raided the address.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who acts to come into possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The person who gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The entity that changes possession, beginning in the possession of the <fen>Donor</fen> and ending up with the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Recipient</fen> comes into possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location at which the Recipient comes into possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which is captured.
The <fen>Agent</fen> brings the <fen>Captive</fen> into custody.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient entity which is responsible for restricting the movement or location of the <fen>Captive</fen>.
When the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist and be associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The entity under discussion, whose states and properties are impacted by its association with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> exists and is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>
The place where the <fen>Entity</fen> is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
This role is the being who has a perceptual experience, not necessarily on purpose. It is typically expressed as an External Argument.
This role is the entity or phenomenon that the perceiver experiences with his or her senses. It is typically expressed as Object with verbs.
The <fen>Body_part</fen> is the location on the <fen>Perceiver_passive</fen>'s body where the perceptual experience  takes place.  It is typically expressed in a PP.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Perceiver_passive</fen> or the <fen>Body_part</fen> perceives the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The general location within which the act of perception takes place.
The volitional agent who without authorization of sender or recipient takes control of a <fen>Theme</fen> that is en route to a destination.
The entity, physical or abstract, construed as traveling from a sender to a goal location, which is taken hold of by the <fen>Interceptor</fen> without permission.
The time period during which the <fen>Interceptor</fen> takes control of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Interceptor</fen> takes control of the <fen>Theme</fen>.

Authorities secured the target <fex>in a private residence</fex>.
<fex>The waiter</fex> smelled something foul in the kitchen.
The waiter smelled <fex>something foul</fex> in the kitchen.
Marlow felt something cold and hard <fex>against the back of his neck</fex>.
Two days later, <fex>an aerial patrol</fex> intercepted an enemy trying the same thing.
They could either sail west down the Channel or north-east to intercept <fex>an enemy making for the Thames estuary</fex>.
The five had been intercepted <fex>after a DFLP attack on March 5</fex>.
She had been intercepted <fex>outside Guy 's room</fex> and would be severely punished.
